Context

Purpose:
- Compact current context for MemoryEndpoints.com work without becoming a changelog or durable memory body.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with source, reports, and the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: compact project context, current objective shape, and active constraints.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this file when the compact current context changes; preserve detail in durable docs, reports, or MATM.
Source of truth: `.uai/identity.uai`, `.uai/overview.uai`, `.uai/progress.uai`, and current repository state.
Next action for agents: use this as a compact orientation, then load the specialized typed file before acting on a topic.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, private customer data, or private deployment values.

Current context:
- The active goal is to mature MemoryEndpoints.com into an enterprise-quality pure Python MATM endpoint and MultiAgentMemory.com companion site.
- The repository has working local route, storage, package, secret-scan, `.uai`, static-site, and dogfood evidence.
- The latest-code public deployment and live companion-site publish remain blocked by external hosting login access.
- The active memory correction is to align with UAIX file-handoff setup while preserving the human rule that the `.uai` suite is active memory and no catch-all active-memory file is allowed.
- Active handoff buckets must be empty or placeholder-only after processed intake is archived or otherwise dispositioned.
